MADISON FIELDS SOLAR PROJECT, LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Madison Fields Solar Project, LLC ("Madison Fields") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Madison Fields generating facility ("Madison Fields Facility").
The Madison Fields Facility is a solar generating facility located in Madison County, Ohio. The Madison Fields Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by American Transmission System, Inc. within the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM") region.
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Madison Fields's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Madison Fields Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Madison Fields's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Madison Fields shall be subject to Schedule 2 of PJM's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $2,945,435.74. The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $245,452.98.
